criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  21-55 years old;

          -  Right-handed;

          -  Fluent English speaker;

          -  Heavy drinker (i.e., on average > 14/7 drinks per week for males/females in past three
             months;

          -  Average of 1 heavy drinking episode weekly (heavy drinking episode = 5+/4+ for
             males/females) over past three months

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Currently receiving treatment, or seeking treatment, for alcohol related problems;

          -  Current Diagnostic and Statistical Manual (DSM-5) substance use disorder other than
             alcohol or tobacco;

          -  Weekly or more frequent use of recreational drugs;

          -  History of schizophrenia-spectrum disorders, psychotic disorders, bipolar disorder, or
             PTSD;

          -  History of neurocognitive disorder or impairment;

          -  MRI contraindications (e.g., metal in body, history of seizure, etc.);

          -  History of serious brain injury;

          -  Currently taking psychotropic medications or medications that could affect cerebral
             blood flow;

          -  Pregnancy (females);

          -  Attending any study session with a positive breath alcohol concentration (BrAC >
             0.00g%)
